The paper discusses the use of swarm robotics for coordinated control of multiple agents, which is a common topic in the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also mentions the bio-inspired nature of the approach, which suggests a possible fit with the Machine Learning (cs.MA) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of a shepherd to guide the swarm of agents implies a focus on control and planning, which aligns with the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of simulation and robotics for various applications, which suggests a possible connection to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
